======== Build steps ========
1. Go to turnin folder
2. run ./buildit; ./OgreApp


======== User Manual ========
Game Mode:
Full Game - Play with AI
Practice  - Hit targets

GamePlay:
Press left mouse button to serve ball.
Move mouse to swing "paddle" in the desired direction
Press left mouse button to shoot
Get 11 points first to win in full-game mode
Hit targets without letting the ball hitting other objects (player, wall, floor) to get combos in practice Mode

Key bindinds:
W,A,S,D - Move Player
LControl - Run
1,2,3 - Player Hit Strength
C - Toggle Camera Mode
R - Restart game
I,J,K,L,U,O - Move Camera
Space - Enter PauseMenu
Esc - Quit game

For More settings:
Go to Pause Menu


======== Project Summary ========
Required Features:
User-controlled "racquet" - Animated Ninja for gamer and Robot for AI
Camera control - Both camera mode toggling and user-controlled camera move
Sound effects - Background sound, sound effects for any collision, controlled by GUI
Physics - Simulated ball movement, kinematic player object, collision detection

Additional Features:
1. AI Opponent
2. PauseMenu GUI, score display
3. Animation when ball hits target

Better than planed:
We made the full-game mode with AI so that we can play "real" tennis now.
Not done:
We did not make a animated paddle object. Instead, we just used the animation of Ninja and Robot mesh.
